    "content_hash": "b2d26964db7bd345",
    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "MARKETING EFFECTIVENESS – STRATEGY \u0026 ENABLEMENT MANAGER\n\nJoin us in our mission to transform the way people shop and eat, where impact, innovation, and growth drives everything we do. Our Brand \u0026 Experience team builds the emotional connection between Deliveroo and our customers, riders, and partners. With a deep understanding of our audience and a passion for creativity, we bring our brand to life across every touchpoint. Whether it’s a push notification, social campaign, or packaging design—we craft compelling experiences that shape perceptions, spark engagement, and make Deliveroo a loved, global brand.\n\nWe’re looking for a Marketing Effectiveness – Strategy \u0026 Enablement Manager to join our London team. In this role, you’ll help us embed data-driven decision-making across our marketing ecosystem, ensuring every creative and media decision drives growth and efficiency at pace.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BE DOING\n\nYou’ll be joining the Marketing Effectiveness team within the Global Marketing Organisation. Our mission is to create a complete understanding of how our activity, channels, and tactics influence customer behaviour and business outcomes.\n\nHere’s what your day-to-day might look like:\n\n - Strategic Partnership: Partner with Brand and Planning teams to embed effectiveness principles throughout the campaign development and planning process.\n\n - Insight Translation: Translate complex model insights (MMM), external studies, and experiment results into clear, actionable recommendations for senior stakeholders.\n\n - Test \u0026 Learn Frameworks: Design and embed a robust Test \u0026 Learn agenda, working with Data Science and media partners to scale learnings across the business.\n\n - Best Practice Advocacy: Champion marketing effectiveness best practices to guide creative development and media planning across the global organisation.\n\n - Measurement Enablement: Develop the tools and communication frameworks that help marketing teams apply data insights in a consistent, practical way.\n\n - Performance Culture: Contribute to a culture of continuous improvement by identifying opportunities to enhance marketing performance and learning integration.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL NEED TO THRIVE\n\nOur ideal candidate will bring strong expertise in some of these areas and curiosity to grow in others:\n\n - Significant Expertise in Marketing Effectiveness: Deep understanding of MMM, brand tracking, and test-and-learn methodologies, ideally within a large consumer brand or agency.\n\n - Analytical Translation: Proven ability to turn complex data into strategic stories and recommendations that influence high-level marketing decisions.\n\n - Cross-Functional Collaboration: Skilled at working effectively with diverse teams, from highly technical Data Scientists to conceptual Creative leads.\n\n - Framework Development: Experience building or embedding marketing processes that drive consistency and improve performance across multiple markets.\n\n - Technical Proficiency: Strong hands-on experience with analytical tools such as Excel/Google Sheets, SQL, or BI platforms like Looker or Tableau.\n\n\nWHY JOIN US?\n\nAt Deliveroo, you’ll do work that matters, solving real-world problems in a three-sided marketplace that’s constantly evolving. We’re food lovers, problem solvers, community builders and more, brought together by a shared drive to make things better. Working here you can expect to:\n\n🔧 Make a visible impact every day Your work directly improves experiences for customers, partners and riders.\n\n🌱 Learn fast in an entrepreneurial environment Work close to the market with autonomy, pace and real responsibility.\n\n🧠 Build a career, not just a role Stretch yourself, develop new skills and grow as the business evolves.\n\n🌎 Deliver together in an inclusive culture Collaborative, values-driven teams that support how you work best.\n\nWe aim to create a fair process that lets your skills shine—our interview typically includes 3-4 stages. Find more about how we hire here https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/.\n\n\n\nOUR GLOBAL STRUCTURE\n\nDeliveroo is now part of DoorDash, bringing together teams with even greater reach, scale, and ambition. Depending on your role, you may collaborate with teammates, systems, and leaders across DoorDash and Wolt. Together, we’re unlocking new possibilities as one global team.\n\n\nDIVERSITY, EQUITY AND INCLUSION\n\nAt Deliveroo, we know that a great workplace reflects the world around us and that true diversity and inclusion make us stronger, more creative, and better at what we do. We’re committed to fostering an environment where everyone can do their best work and feel they belong.\n\nWe believe in equality of opportunity and welcome candidates from all backgrounds regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, socio-economic background, religion, or belief.\n\nIf you have a disability or long-term health condition and need support to apply for one of our roles, or require any reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, you’ll have the opportunity to let us know once you’ve submitted your application. We’ll share details on how to request support so we can ensure you have a fair and equitable experience.\n\nIf you’re excited about making a real impact in a fast-moving marketplace and growing your career alongside ambitious, supportive teams, we’d love to hear from you!",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
